Interface MatchedPath<V,T>

Type Parameters:
V - The type of the elements for OnRoad results

public interface MatchedPath<V,T>
The result of applying a PathMatcher to observations.

See also TransitionProbabilityStrategy, which may compute transition data.

    • transitions

      List<com.here.platform.location.core.mapmatching.MatchedPath.Transition<T>> transitions()
      The Transitions between results if they were computed during matching.
      • Some results may be skipped, meaning there may be no Transition going from or to that result. For example, a path containing an Unknown result could contain transitions that skip this result. That way, the transitions give a consistent picture of the path traveled while ignoring the Unknown, likely caused by incorrect data.
      • For any transition t, t.from must be less than t.to.
      • For two consecutive transitions t1 and t2,t1.to must be less than or equal to t2.from (the transitions must be sorted in ascending order)
